    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required credibility levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level of 3 due to single ASTM F1717 test configuration; this gap is accepted given the prescriptive standardized protocol and demonstrated low sensitivity of titanium construct response to quasi-static rate variation. All three pre-specified QoI acceptance criteria satisfied (max percent difference 3.1%, max E/uval 0.88). FEA ensemble agreement across three independent codes provides additional confidence. The overall credibility package is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level decision for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
